{"id":"61aad99b-76f0-42e5-ab8b-dc3600e717ae","title":"1547: To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"1e7cf3bb-92e1-483b-9de7-546fc1137183","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, ... [1547].","standoffProperties":[{"id":"34027724-a949-42b4-9b2f-42bad2209331","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":3,"value":"8532f2fa-b614-4eed-9eae-586327f6a15a","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"a31c17e6-ad6d-42f9-83c6-95a9131755ec","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"fdc70a90-55e8-4d4b-b390-a1535f6cdfd7","type":"codex/time-reference","start":16,"end":19,"value":"8cd154e0-c397-48ad-b09b-34bd561309d9","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"e3b78998-4575-4dcc-ac9d-d288821f9f07","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"30eca988-d6b8-4470-8c80-3e42b415a9b9","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"9ea89f9c-4c85-4ee1-9f13-d3d7ae8508b8","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"1f590190-c810-4bca-b0af-4e8edc6cf7d5","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"0d1e3fbd-b3cd-408e-be9b-4f6dfe455367","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":1,"value":"0c663cc2-dd9f-40ce-b17b-734e41b369ef","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"a2a9b985-3cb8-4c17-8603-217ffd8381e2","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"0003bdf8-7b7d-4890-94ff-01bdcebcfeb6","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"ee8d875b-dfa4-4d8b-8dee-afd410c424d7","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0With regard to that house of the Corsi, thou writest to say that we had best be in\u00A0no hurry about buying as it is not yet finished,\u00A0and that it seems to thee advisable to proceed\u00A0instead with the matter of the shop, as thou hast\u00A0found someone to go into partnership with thee. To me it seems\u00A0\u2014\u00A0provided the external walls are being soundly built and there are no mortgages on the property\u00A0\u2014\u00A0that we ought to buy it, so as to dispose of that money. The internal fittings of the\u00A0house could be carried out piece by piece afterwards. After the house has been bought there may still remain enough money to enable thee to set up the shop with a partner, although this does not seem to me the proper time for such a speculative undertaking. I do not know of any family in Florence that has prospered by other means than the possession of landed property. However, do as seemeth to thee best: whatever ye may do concerns yourselves alone. As to the almsgiving, methinks thou art over neglectful: if thou wouldst not give away my money for the repose of thy father\u0027s soul, how much less wouldst thou give of thine own? Salute Messer Francesco [Fattucci] for me: thank him and say, with reference to thy marrying, that I am waiting for a friend of mine, now absent from Rome, who has three or four propositions to put before me. I will let him know the result, and we shall see if\u00A0anything suitable offers.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"6d98c524-0f56-4338-9e5d-b981a371f56f","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":7,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"f7d27e18-6a79-43a3-8504-b976cd4b23d9","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"03fc8216-d2ef-497f-8182-bae4f1cf36f4","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":32,"end":36,"value":"a7ca02e2-998f-444f-8b07-64f8240620a3","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"08